Description: This package implements a microbiome genome-wide association study (mGWAS) workflow based on the PALM framework. 
       Host genetic variants are modeled as covariates of interest in regression-based association testing to identify associations 
       between microbial features and host genotypes. The package provides end-to-end utilities for input checking, null model fitting, 
       association testing, and result summarization, and is designed to support large-scale analyses across multiple microbial features 
       and genetic variants. The workflow is compatible with containerized and high-performance computing environments.
